Package gameClient

  • Class Summary
    Class Description
    Agent
    This class is used for a player (Agent) in the Pokemon game, The role of the player is to collect a quantity of Pokemon objects on a graph.
    Arena
    The Arena class is used to store the update information coming from the server regarding the game in real time.
    Ex2
    Running class of the game Option 1 - Run through file .jar Option 2 - Run through the CMD
    GameFrame
    This class represents a GUI class to present game on a graph.
    GamePanel
    The GamePanel class is used for drawing the components on the frame of the game Contains: drawing information about the game, graph, Pokemon, agents, and refreshing the components each time.
    LoginGameFrame
    This class is used for the login window of the game (GUI) Containing within it the inputs of ID and a stage in the game and beyond the beginning of the game.
    MainGame
    This class presents an entire course of the game.
    Pokemon
    The Pokemon class is designed for the Pokemon game Each Pokemon object is in a random position on the graph, and contains a value and type.
